        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 6:51PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 650 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southwest of St. Jo, or 13 miles east of Bowie, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nocona, Muenster, St. Jo, Lake Nocona, Lake Muenster, Hubert H Moss
Lake, Nocona Hills, Montague, Prairie Point, Bulcher, Capps Corner,
Illinois Bend, Forestburg, Marysville, Spanish Fort, Sivells Bend,
Mallard, Bonita, and Rosston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
